title.narrative: OUTPUT 7.4 COMMUNICATION, ADVOCACY AND PARTNERSHIPS

description.narrative: Output 4 (Communications, advocacy and partnerships): UNICEF staff and partners have the guidance, tools and resources for effective communication on child rights issues with partners and stakeholders, which contributes to Communication And Advocacy, Cross-Sectoral - Human Rights, Cross-Sectoral - Other Programme Areas, Cross-Sectoral - Other Programme Areas (Covid), Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Programmes are efficiently designed, coordinated, managed and supported to meet quality programming standards in achieving results for children in development and humanitarian settings.

description.narrative: In the second year of the COVID-19 pandemic, creating demand for the COVID-19 vaccines while promoting key prevention behaviours through an integrated risk communication and community engagement strategy remained a key focus of UNICEF’s agenda. At the same time, communication and engagement efforts continued to support UNICEF’s regular advocacy and programme outcomes through public campaigns on broadcast and digital media, influencers engagement and new partnerships with civil society, community-based organizations and youth-led networks.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/01/2022
